  "prompt": "Why does the Justin Bieber video Baby have more dislikes than likes?",
  "response": "The music video for Justin Bieber's song \"Baby\" has a notable number of dislikes on YouTube for several reasons:\n\n1. **Overexposure and Polarizing Effect**: At the time of its release, \"Baby\" was an extremely popular song that received heavy airplay. Overexosure can lead to a backlash, with some people expressing their fatigue or annoyance by disliking the video.\n\n2. **Target Demographic**: The song and video were primarily targeted at a younger, mostly teenage audience. While this demographic may have contributed to a high number of likes, it also meant that the video was not as well-received by older audiences or those outside of Bieber's core fan base, leading to dislikes.\n\n3. **Change in Musical Trends**: As musical tastes evolve and change, some people may revisit older, once-popular songs with a more critical ear, leading to new dislikes over time.\n\n4. **YouTube as a Platform for Expression**: YouTube's like and dislike buttons serve as a way for users to express their opinions. For some, disliking a video can be a form of protest or a way to express disapproval of the artist, the music, or the video content.\n\n5. **Cultural and Social Factors**: As with any public figure, Justin Bieber's actions outside of his music career have influenced public perception. At various times, Bieber has been involved in controversies that may have contributed to people disliking his content as a form of protest.\n\n6. **Competition with Other Records**: \"Baby\" was released at a time when it was competing with other songs that people may have preferred. Some users might have disliked the video because they felt other music deserved the attention \"Baby\" was getting.\n\n7. **Trolling and Coordinated Dislike Campaigns**: There have been instances where internet users coordinated to dislike a video as a form of trolling or to make a statement, which could have affected the \"Baby\" video's dislike count.\n\nIt's important to note that despite the number of dislikes, \"Baby\" has also amassed a very large number of views and likes, indicating that it has been a successful and impactful piece of pop culture. Likes and dislikes are just one metric of a video's reception and don't necessarily reflect the overall cultural significance or quality of the content.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
